<span id="freeTextContainer11320673534891388170">(orginially 4.5*) <br/><br/>What a tragedy- what a mess! Definitely looking forward to studying this in detail, because I feel like reading this once and rating it immediately doesn&apos;t do justice to this masterpiece. I know that I missed a lot reading it for the first time round so yes, as I said, a lot of potential for further study!<br/><br/>5* <br/><br/>As I suspected, I&apos;m enjoying studying this play more than actually reading it!<br/><br/>edit 19.05.16: ha it&apos;s actually quite hilarious how obsessed I am with this play now. After se</span>
  <span id="freeText11320673534891388170" style="display:none">(orginially 4.5*) <br /><br />What a tragedy- what a mess! Definitely looking forward to studying this in detail, because I feel like reading this once and rating it immediately doesn't do justice to this masterpiece. I know that I missed a lot reading it for the first time round so yes, as I said, a lot of potential for further study!<br /><br />5* <br /><br />As I suspected, I'm enjoying studying this play more than actually reading it!<br /><br />edit 19.05.16: ha it's actually quite hilarious how obsessed I am with this play now. After seeing the National Theatre Live recording of it from the West End starring Mark Strong et al, I have become so attached to this play. I can't artciulate my thoughts at the moment because I am so in awe...!</span>
